\title{zhncommandR: Audit and Analysis Dashboard for Haematological Oncology Cohorts}
\description{
Reads tumour-documentation spreadsheets from haematological tumour centres
and computes quality and coverage indicators, OPS-8-544 complex chemotherapy
block counts, OPS-1-941 complex diagnostics counts, Kaplan-Meier analyses,
oncoprint and cytogenetics summaries, plus an interactive Shiny dashboard
for auditor live evaluation.
}
\details{
The entry point for interactive use is \code{\link[=zhn_run_app]{zhn_run_app()}}. Programmatic users
will mostly call the readers (\code{\link[=zhn_read_cohort]{zhn_read_cohort()}}, \code{\link[=zhn_read_therapy]{zhn_read_therapy()}},
\code{\link[=zhn_read_diagnostics]{zhn_read_diagnostics()}}) followed by the parsers
(\code{\link[=zhn_prepare_therapy_blocks]{zhn_prepare_therapy_blocks()}}, \code{\link[=zhn_prepare_diagnostic_blocks]{zhn_prepare_diagnostic_blocks()}},
\code{\link[=zhn_parse_oncoprint]{zhn_parse_oncoprint()}}, \code{\link[=zhn_parse_cytogenetics]{zhn_parse_cytogenetics()}}).

A fully synthetic example cohort is bundled and accessible via
\code{\link[=zhn_example_path]{zhn_example_path()}}.
}
